Happy dad moment tonight! Took our first walk out in the world this evening. It was a warm night in Davis so we kept it short but it was nice to emerge from the confines of our house sized swaddle.

Se Hwa (세화) slept through the whole walk, @townesandsimone snoofed every flower, and @emilymeineke and I just took it all in, our first of countless walks as a family. 

We are feeling so fortunate to have our community. 

If anyone is interested in the origins of the name Se Hwa (세화), it translates to queen of the oceans but more importantly it was my paternal grandmother’s name. She raised me, and she embodied love. 

When I was in elementary school, probably 5-6 years old, a local High Point photographer got a photo of my grandmother holding my hand and walking me down the half mile dirt road that was our driveway. She walked down that driveway every afternoon to wait for me to get dropped off by the school bus so she could walk me back to our house. I wish I had that photograph still so I could show my daughter Se Hwa one day, the kind of person her namesake was.

Week 1+2 days: Parenthood is anxiety ridden and endlessly rewarding. In the middle of the night, every little peep and squeak takes my head to a dark place and at the same moment brings a heart filled smile. I spend hours in the middle of the night just staring at her hoping if I stay fast with my gaze, she won’t grow up.

I wish there was a word in the English language that was different than the word “love” for this feeling. It’s not just love it’s something so different and deep. I love her. 

I see Emily in her. I see me in her. She is perfect from these two imperfects.
So hard to leave these two behind to fly to Lincoln, NE for tomorrow’s show. See you all this weekend.

Bottles and Bread

Thought I’d see if I can still remember how to make a sour dough batard. 

I started a fresh starter before I left for tour this past weekend and came back to it nice and active. 

This morning as Se Hwa had her post feeding sleep I started baking off the loaves I cold fermented last night for 12 hours. One flopped, this one did great. Nice ear on it and the smells(!), oh how I’ve missed the smell of freshly baked bread. #breadmaking #sourdough

Definitely proofed my pizza dough too long today and lost the shape. Good thing ugly pizza still tastes good! 

Also gave wood fire baking in the @fontanaforniusa a try today. The olive loaf to the right in the first photo definitely looks different but I am not too upset with how it turned out. I think I need more height inside the oven to get the right bake. Next time I’ll try a cold final ferment to see if the loaf holds its shape better in the oven. Anyone have any other tips for wood fire baking? How do you keep you humidity level high in the first 20m?

1: 2 sourdough batards next to the wood fired olive loaf ala @tartinebakery 
2: sungold and honey pie
3: mushroom and onion vegan pie

In the oven I currently have a bunch of leftover veg from my fridge drying out to make veggie stock tomorrow.

A couple days before leaving for this tour Emily and I got to go watch @chiaramondavi do her thing bringing in the first of the grapes for Se Hwa’s vintage of @sentiumwines we got to taste some of the freshly pressed juice, watch the highly skilled lift workers and team preparing everything for what will be a special vintage for @emilymeineke and me. 

Chiara held up clusters of grapes that we got to sample. She explained the ripeness, the skins, the color variances due to sun exposure on one side of a cluster, partially ripe clusters, etc. It was all a part of wine making that we have never experienced and it was fascinating to say the least.

It has been so nice to have our friends @_halasaleh_ and Eli here to take a bit of the feeding/burping/bouncing/changing/walking/cleaning/cooking….duties off our plates.

Everyone help me thank Si and Jin for all their amazing love and help!
The touring year has ended. Thank You for another great year. On to being a full time dad to Se Hwa and @townesandsimone. Look at the smiles on those pups.

Today was a big day for little Se Hwa. She got to finally come see and meet the amazing people @communityfitnessdavis she had visits from her friends @_legendarius__ and @xandra.warriorprincess and then she had her first public outing @sudwerkbrew celebrating @insta.justus’s birthday. She’s tuckered out now and sleeping (hopefully for several hours). 

Everyone got a preview of her bear costume which she’s been saving for her @yayoikusama_ exhibit visit on Halloween @sfmoma.

@emilymeineke got this shot of me “camping” with Se Hwa.

This whole being a dad thing isn’t for everybody but I, for one, am loving every heart wrenching, sleepless, dirty, hungry, fussy, part of it.
You know Emily and I are huge @peteholmes fans, so we are super excited to sit down tonight and watch his new special that released on @netflix today.

During a layover in SLC, Joe Kwon jumped on The Gnar Stool, along with Gnarly CEO, Eli Kerr sitting in for Dr. Shannon O’Grady.  Joe has spent the last 17 years as the beloved cellist with The Avett Brothers. While many folks may know him for his unique style of dancing across the stage while simultaneously playing impeccable cello, what you may not know is how he became a fulltime musician, what it’s like being a first time dad, and what his latest poop story is. Joe is also a total fitness nut, a food fanatic through and through as well as daydreamer skier. What even is that? Take a seat to find out and learn a thing or two about what’s making Joe Kwon tick these days. #pushyourpossible #gnarly #thegnarstoolpodcast #joekwon

@townesandsimone don’t get nearly enough love these days but they are the best keepers of their baby sister. Se Hwa is currently in her bassinet sleeping while these two make sure those evil squirrels outside don’t infiltrate the living-room.

These two knuckleheads are just so sweet. It’s such a shame pitties get such a bum rap. 

#pitty Townes “part time bad boy” and Simone “the perfect one” had a nice play time this morning while we enjoyed the humidity some cool air brought in this morning. Se Hwa sat by the spa with us while we made our NC plans for this week. My mom hasn’t yet been able to meet Se Hwa so this will be her first time getting to spend some time with her. 

We are stressed about Se Hwa’s first plane ride so send over some life hacks we should know about.
@townesandsimone Townes got in Se Hwa’s bassinet that I set up for her then promptly gave me the middle finger 🖕🏻 with his eyes when I asked him to make some room for Se Hwa. @doglifebythule

Napa you are so beautiful. The wine making is still going on right now but luckily we got to see the vineyards as they turn their beautiful fall hue. 

We took Se Hwa and @townesandsimone up to Napa for Thanksgiving and got to pop up our @thule tent setup for the first time. Townes was a fan (Simone never wants to get in that tent ever again). 

This December @emilymeineke and I will be driving Townes, Simone, and @kwon.sehwa to NC. We’ll be hoping to stop at some great off-roadside spots for morning coffees and feedings.

We’ll document the trip and let you know how feasible a cross-country trek in an EV(with a 4 month old and 2 dogs) actually is.
